cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new adversarial attack method for deep neural networks that is based on a randomized search scheme and does not rely on local gradient information. The attack is evaluated on image classification tasks using deep networks, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, given the focus on machine learning and optimization techniques, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) due to the nature of adversarial attacks. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
